article.headline: Morgan St. 53, Winston-Salem St. 50
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Jamar Smith scored four of his nine points in the final three minutes while Ronald Timus scored a team-high 13 points and had seven rebounds as Morgan State held off Winston-Salem State 53-50 Friday night. Boubacar Coly chipped in seven points and grabbed nine rebounds as Morgan State (3-9, 1-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) snapped a three-game losing streak. Winston-Salem (1-18), which rallied back from a 10-point deficit in the second half, led 49-47 with 4:37 remaining following back-to-back three-point baskets as the shot clock expired from Darius Floyd and Brian Fisher. Fisher had a chance to tie the game at 52 with 34 seconds remaining, but missed both of his free-throw attempts. Morgan jumped out to an early 22-11 first-half lead following a basket from Joseph McLean with 8:15 left in the first half. However, Winston-Salem responded with a 13-3 run over the next seven minutes as the Rams pulled within 25-24 after Jamal Durham connected on one of two free-throw attempts with 1:33 left in the first half. Poor shooting hurt Winston-Salem all night as the Rams shot 31.8 percent in the first half and 32.7 percent for the game. Fisher scored a team-high 14 points while Floyd scored 13 for Winston-Salem, which has lost 15 in a row. Winston-Salem is an independent team that is in the second year of a five-year transition from Division II to Division I. They will become the 12th member of the MEAC next season.
